It's raining heavily. [Chapter 3]

55
00:03:42,940 --> 00:03:45,660
How did you know it was going to rain?

56
00:03:45,660 --> 00:03:47,700
It was said.

57
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:49,270
By whom?

58
00:03:49,270 --> 00:03:51,730
He tells me the weather forecast every morning.

59
00:03:51,730 --> 00:03:54,210
A handy little thing.

60
00:03:54,210 --> 00:03:56,850
Sometimes they're better than humans.

61
00:03:59,070 --> 00:04:01,610
Did you meet with the important client?

62
00:04:01,610 --> 00:04:03,440
I don't think they're here.

63
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:08,060
If I had known there was going to be a party, I wouldn't have come.

64
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:11,910
I'm free to go home now, aren't I?

65
00:04:11,910 --> 00:04:13,320
Not yet.

66
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:15,240
Hey, are you kidding me?

67
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:17,150
You may have offered job security.

68
00:04:17,150 --> 00:04:19,750
But you don't respect my fundamental rights.

69
00:04:19,750 --> 00:04:22,530
If you're not going to abandon me, at least feed me.

70
00:04:22,530 --> 00:04:25,130
I haven't even had lunch.

71
00:04:25,130 --> 00:04:27,290
I'm hungry!

72
00:04:27,290 --> 00:04:29,750
I have no energy left.

73
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:33,580
You look full of energy.

74
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:43,610
See? I told you.

75
00:04:43,610 --> 00:04:44,800
Why are you being so friendly with me...?

76
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,450
