229
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:58,100
You weren't talking about me, were you?

230
00:13:58,100 --> 00:14:00,600
You're too sensitive.

231
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:01,970
Me. I was talking about myself.

232
00:14:01,970 --> 00:14:04,970
I act too much the way I want to.

233
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:06,740
Objectifying oneself.

234
00:14:06,740 --> 00:14:08,900
At least you're good at this.

235
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:17,620
Let's begin the meeting.

236
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:21,950
You must understand the importance of the renovation project.

237
00:14:21,950 --> 00:14:23,960
It will start in Seoul and spread nationwide.

238
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:26,030
The beginning will be the most important thing.

239
00:14:26,030 --> 00:14:29,610
That's why we chose the Gangnam store.

240
00:14:29,610 --> 00:14:31,240
[Renovation Candidate No. 1, Gangnam Store]

241
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:32,840
Is it the Admiral store or the Gangnam store?

242
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:35,160
Gangnam is the center of commerce.

243
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:38,760
But our store's sales were lower than the others.

244
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:40,820
We need a refresh right now.

245
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:42,550
Failure would be very risky.

246
00:14:42,550 --> 00:14:45,320
If we succeed, the reward will be great.

247
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:48,310
Once we open the way, sales are guaranteed.

248
00:14:48,310 --> 00:14:51,670
The next candidate is a safer option.

249
00:14:51,670 --> 00:14:55,330
No problem. I was thinking of the Gangnam store too.

250
00:14:55,330 --> 00:14:57,840
We all agree. Why waste time?

251
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,910
Let's go to the Gangnam store.

252
00:14:59,910 --> 00:15:01,230
Okay.

253
00:15:04,230 --> 00:15:06,140
Where are you going?

254
00:15:06,140 --> 00:15:08,530
To the Gangnam store. That's the selected store.

255
00:15:08,530 --> 00:15:11,300
I need to assess the region properly.

256
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:14,460
- Um... - What?

257
00:15:15,250 --> 00:15:19,560
They didn't plan this together beforehand, did they?

258
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:22,690
I know. They completely agreed.

259
00:15:31,780 --> 00:15:32,680
[Grace]

260
00:15:36,550 --> 00:15:38,900
Do you want to sleep with me?

261
00:15:38,900 --> 00:15:40,780
Shall we do it?

262
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:45,310
Damn it.

263
00:15:46,460 --> 00:15:48,500
I am good.

264
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:58,880
You've probably heard about the renovation project.

265
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:01,790
Yes, I heard that our store might be the first.

266
00:16:01,790 --> 00:16:03,730
It will start today.

267
00:16:03,730 --> 00:16:05,120
Ah, I understand.

268
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:07,450
Let's work hard, Branch Manager.

269
00:16:07,450 --> 00:16:08,520
Yes, of course.

270
00:16:08,520 --> 00:16:11,310
We will research customers and measure demand.

271
00:16:11,310 --> 00:16:13,420
Will this be enough?

272
00:16:14,130 --> 00:16:15,550
Sir?

273
00:16:16,130 --> 00:16:19,220
The main goal of the renovation is to acquire new customers.

274
00:16:19,220 --> 00:16:22,940
Conduct a survey beyond existing customers.

275
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:27,120
The brands, products, services, and facilities they want.

276
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:29,880
How can we ask about non-customers?

277
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:32,470
Make them willing to participate.

278
00:16:32,470 --> 00:16:34,700
Spend money or overindulge.

279
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:36,680
There's no need to be conservative.

280
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:38,960
Understood. We'll start immediately.

281
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:40,650
Okay. You can go.

282
00:16:40,650 --> 00:16:42,090
Excuse me? Is that all?

283
00:16:42,090 --> 00:16:46,080
If I were with you, they would realize that a high-ranking official was here.

284
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:49,050
I want to evaluate the store as it is.

285
00:16:49,050 --> 00:16:51,410
Alright then. Feel free to explore.

286
00:16:51,410 --> 00:16:53,720
We will stay in touch.

287
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:01,160
This...

288
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:03,700
You recognized it. That's the brand I use.

289
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:07,760
I only use their products.

290
00:17:10,870 --> 00:17:13,710
The lead singer of my favorite band is like that too.

291
00:17:13,710 --> 00:17:15,950
Ah, I understand.

292
00:17:15,950 --> 00:17:20,720
I noticed the slanted letter on the sign.

293
00:17:21,570 --> 00:17:22,980
You're observant.

294
00:17:22,980 --> 00:17:25,030
But you didn't notice the brand of my sunglasses.

295
00:17:25,030 --> 00:17:26,960
I will inform the employee.

296
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:29,190
These sunglasses cost one million won.

297
00:17:29,190 --> 00:17:31,100
But how can the repair cost 800,000?

298
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:33,610
Feet and screws...

299
00:17:33,610 --> 00:17:36,410
It was designed by a craftsman.

300
00:17:36,410 --> 00:17:41,300
The repair needs to be done at the center in Italy and then sent back to you.

301
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:44,750
Still. You're not doing it again.

302
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:46,340
800,000 won is no joke.

303
00:17:46,340 --> 00:17:50,030
They basically need to be rebuilt.

304
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:54,520
Who are you?

305
00:17:54,520 --> 00:17:59,690
If you don't understand their value, you have no right to wear them.

306
00:17:59,690 --> 00:18:05,000
Who are you? Why are you deciding whether I have a right or not?

307
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,400
What is it?

308
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:28,390
Someone who understands the value of the product.

309
00:18:34,740 --> 00:18:37,120
Whatever. Whatever. I don't care.

310
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:40,980
If you came here to shop, buy yourself a pair and leave.

311
00:18:40,980 --> 00:18:42,660
You're getting on my nerves.

312
00:18:42,660 --> 00:18:47,540
Trying to annoy you? Are you serious...? Excuse me.

313
00:18:47,540 --> 00:18:49,100
How are things?

314
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:52,550
It looked better on you than it used to.

315
00:18:52,550 --> 00:18:55,990
Are you telling me to buy a new pair now?

316
00:18:55,990 --> 00:18:59,190
Are you trying to annoy me even more?

317
00:18:59,190 --> 00:19:05,760
It doesn't deserve any of this... You have to wait a long time for repairs.

318
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:11,310
If it's going to cost the same price, shouldn't you buy a pair that suits you better?

319
00:19:11,310 --> 00:19:12,790
I work at Yongseong.

320
00:19:12,790 --> 00:19:14,070
I can give you a discount.

321
00:19:14,070 --> 00:19:17,320
Then they would be worth 650,000 won.

322
00:19:18,120 --> 00:19:19,320
Say what?

323
00:19:19,320 --> 00:19:22,160
Try it briefly.

324
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:24,120
Just hold it over your face.

325
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:26,180
Let me show you the mirror.

326
00:19:26,180 --> 00:19:27,690
Let me see.

327
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:01,110
Great.

328
00:20:08,110 --> 00:20:11,260
I think I'll buy a new pair.

329
00:20:11,260 --> 00:20:13,090
- Would you like to? - Of course.

330
00:20:13,090 --> 00:20:15,820
Give her a new pair.

331
00:20:16,490 --> 00:20:18,550
Wow, that's great.

332
00:20:21,940 --> 00:20:23,860
It wasn't that he didn't understand its value.

333
00:20:23,860 --> 00:20:26,200
He couldn't afford the fee.

334
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:28,740
Still, we shouldn't have paid that much attention to him.

335
00:20:28,740 --> 00:20:30,590
That was too much, even for you.

336
00:20:30,590 --> 00:20:31,870
I know.

337
00:20:31,870 --> 00:20:34,790
I was about to make an unforgivable mistake.

338
00:20:34,790 --> 00:20:39,010
It might have been one of the few mistakes I've made in my life.

339
00:20:39,010 --> 00:20:41,750
But you stopped me.

340
00:20:42,270 --> 00:20:45,780
Thank you, but this is a bit...

341
00:20:45,780 --> 00:20:47,940
I've never seen his naked face.

342
00:20:47,940 --> 00:20:49,950
I didn't recognize him.

343
00:20:51,010 --> 00:20:52,830
Sir?

344
00:20:52,830 --> 00:20:54,560
Kim?

345
00:20:56,390 --> 00:21:00,090
The singer at the concert? Is that right?

346
00:21:00,090 --> 00:21:02,180
Great. You should have said something.

347
00:21:02,180 --> 00:21:04,270
You're a fan.

348
00:21:04,270 --> 00:21:06,280
True, it was a secret.

349
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:10,730
Are you just going to leave him like that?

350
00:21:10,730 --> 00:21:14,350
Shall I get your autograph?

351
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,050
No problem.

352
00:21:19,730 --> 00:21:21,610
Just wait.

353
00:21:21,610 --> 00:21:22,980
Ben...

354
00:21:22,980 --> 00:21:25,440
A pen. I don't have a pen.

355
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:27,130
Al.

356
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,420
Excuse me!

357
00:21:37,970 --> 00:21:39,490
Excuse me.

358
00:21:40,160 --> 00:21:41,640
One second.

359
00:21:42,310 --> 00:21:44,190
I watched your show once.

360
00:21:44,190 --> 00:21:45,970
I'm a huge fan of yours.

361
00:21:45,970 --> 00:21:47,590
Can I get an autograph?

362
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:48,630
Certainly.

363
00:21:48,630 --> 00:21:50,520
I didn't recognize you.

364
00:21:50,520 --> 00:21:51,800
You're so cool.

365
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,590
Thank you.

366
00:21:57,270 --> 00:21:58,520
Photograph?

367
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:00,520
One second.

368
00:22:01,540 --> 00:22:06,430
I told the director that I admired him, and he offered to take a photo with me.

369
00:22:06,430 --> 00:22:07,420
A photo?

370
00:22:07,420 --> 00:22:10,830
It would be nice if you could be inside, but you can't tell anyone.

371
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:14,200
I'll take one for you. Be satisfied with me.

372
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:36,590
I'll take the picture now.

373
00:22:36,590 --> 00:22:39,880
One two three.

374
00:22:56,560 --> 00:22:58,440
What's this?

375
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:00,880
Only my hair is visible.

376
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:03,280
Because I'm not a fan.

377
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:04,950
Message me the photo.

378
00:23:04,950 --> 00:23:07,170
Maybe I won't throw it away.

379
00:23:08,620 --> 00:23:10,910
I got your autograph and a photo.

380
00:23:10,910 --> 00:23:12,840
But you treated me like this.

381
00:23:12,840 --> 00:23:14,010
I know.

382
00:23:14,010 --> 00:23:16,880
I got an autograph and a photo.

383
00:23:17,420 --> 00:23:19,770
You don't need to thank me.

384
00:23:19,770 --> 00:23:21,660
I admire him for a reason.

385
00:23:21,660 --> 00:23:26,290
Not only is he a great singer, but he's also a wonderful person.

386
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:30,030
Do you love him that much?

387
00:23:30,830 --> 00:23:32,220
Are you kidding me?

388
00:23:32,220 --> 00:23:34,450
I'm jealous.

389
00:23:34,990 --> 00:23:38,160
To feel passionate about something.

390
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:40,570
I think it's something valuable.

391
00:23:40,570 --> 00:23:43,390
Finding what you love is hard.

392
00:23:43,390 --> 00:23:46,740
It's hard to love something for a long time.

393
00:23:49,270 --> 00:23:51,420
For that reason...

394
00:23:51,420 --> 00:23:54,350
Enjoy it as much as you want.

395
00:23:55,760 --> 00:23:59,607
No matter what others think, enjoy your hobby...

396
00:23:59,619 --> 00:24:03,800
...I don't think receiving it makes you a bad heir.

397
00:24:05,950 --> 00:24:10,500
The heir chooses the president, not you.

398
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:14,070
Do you think I don't know this?

399
00:24:14,070 --> 00:24:17,040
Is this how you answer...?

400
00:24:17,790 --> 00:24:19,350
Anyway.

401
00:24:19,350 --> 00:24:22,410
Be careful. You'll get wet.

402
00:25:15,390 --> 00:25:17,370
Get a loan!

403
00:25:17,370 --> 00:25:19,220
Rainbow.

404
00:25:21,930 --> 00:25:24,740
I hadn't seen him in a while.

405
00:25:48,120 --> 00:25:50,150
Beautiful.

406
00:25:51,490 --> 00:25:53,790
I'm enjoying it...

407
00:25:55,430 --> 00:25:57,550
That's enough already.

408
00:25:58,690 --> 00:26:00,360
Or...

409
00:26:01,010 --> 00:26:03,100
I'll try to enjoy myself more freely...

410
00:26:03,100 --> 00:26:05,030
At least in front of you.

411
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:39,850
He's not bad at his job.

412
00:26:40,620 --> 00:26:42,910
That is, Bayan Baek Su Jeong.

413
00:26:42,910 --> 00:26:44,770
You said it wasn't important...

414
00:26:44,770 --> 00:26:47,070
And that it must be destroyed.

415
00:26:47,070 --> 00:26:50,830
Not anymore. It doesn't look bad anymore.

416
00:26:50,830 --> 00:26:53,360
You said it was a talent I would appreciate.

417
00:26:53,360 --> 00:26:55,290
Isn't it?

418
00:26:55,290 --> 00:26:59,120
I knew I understood your type.

419
00:27:10,510 --> 00:27:12,450
He's not bad at his job.

420
00:27:12,450 --> 00:27:15,830
- Who? - Director Ban Ju Yeon.

421
00:27:15,830 --> 00:27:19,460
He makes decisions quickly, is highly motivated, and has a good intuition.

422
00:27:20,340 --> 00:27:24,040
I think you called him a rebel this morning.

423
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:27,240
I think we have two directors now.

424
00:27:28,280 --> 00:27:31,520
I thought you didn't like him, Team Leader.

425
00:27:31,520 --> 00:27:32,830
I thought so too.

426
00:27:32,830 --> 00:27:34,370
There's nothing to like or dislike.

427
00:27:34,370 --> 00:27:36,560
He/She just needs to be good at his/her job.

428
00:27:53,190 --> 00:27:57,300
[Curved]

429
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:04,720
It makes you wake up immediately.

430
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:07,800
This is best when working late hours.

431
00:28:13,410 --> 00:28:14,710
Do you work late?

432
00:28:14,710 --> 00:28:16,310
Well, yes.

433
00:28:16,310 --> 00:28:18,500
After working in the field, I had work to do.

434
00:28:18,500 --> 00:28:20,280
I wanted to finish it before I left.

435
00:28:20,280 --> 00:28:24,920
If I work late due to a sudden schedule change, how will that show me?

436
00:28:24,920 --> 00:28:28,150
Don't work late and leave without a reason.

437
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:31,910
Well...

438
00:28:31,910 --> 00:28:35,550
Who would tell someone to quit their job so rudely?

439
00:28:36,140 --> 00:28:40,320
Besides, it was too late to take the dress to the dry cleaner.

440
00:28:40,320 --> 00:28:42,460
You should keep it safe.

441
00:28:42,460 --> 00:28:44,740
Excuse me? Why?

442
00:28:44,740 --> 00:28:47,080
I don't need it...

443
00:28:48,210 --> 00:28:50,300
And it was beautiful.

444
00:28:53,180 --> 00:28:55,800
A dress. I mean, a dress.

445
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:57,930
So, the dress.

446
00:28:59,230 --> 00:29:00,950
Peace.

447
00:29:10,280 --> 00:29:12,240
Comic.

448
00:29:26,750 --> 00:29:29,510
You're coming to my sanctuary.

449
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:44,720
- Who is this? - Bbanjju! Sweetheart!

450
00:29:54,360 --> 00:29:57,570
My face blushes when I see you.

451
00:29:57,570 --> 00:30:01,000
He doesn't really resemble her.

452
00:30:06,370 --> 00:30:09,220
Please thank your mother for me.

453
00:30:20,650 --> 00:30:23,890
What are you smiling at? How annoying.

454
00:30:24,820 --> 00:30:26,330
What is it?

455
00:30:26,330 --> 00:30:27,410
Did I smile?

456
00:30:27,410 --> 00:30:30,820
How stupid do you have to be not to notice?

457
00:30:33,860 --> 00:30:36,930
I've never experienced this before.

458
00:30:38,570 --> 00:30:44,470
Hey, do you think fate is a real thing?

459
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:49,660
We were made for each other.

460
00:30:49,660 --> 00:30:50,940
My destiny.

461
00:30:50,940 --> 00:30:52,110
Your existence.

462
00:30:52,110 --> 00:30:54,270
His very existence disgusts me.

463
00:30:54,270 --> 00:30:58,470
Stay sealed forever, you little cow!

464
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:02,370
You're in a dangerous situation. Be careful.

465
00:31:02,370 --> 00:31:07,350
Falling dangerously in love with someone will cause you unbearable pain.

466
00:31:08,890 --> 00:31:12,340
You just...

467
00:31:12,340 --> 00:31:15,640
You were thinking about your first love, weren't you?

468
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:18,620
I will relieve you of your pain now.

469
00:31:18,620 --> 00:31:21,500
Hey, tough!

470
00:31:44,240 --> 00:31:46,640
Is it nice?

471
00:31:49,340 --> 00:31:52,800
I would never wear it, and it doesn't even suit me.

472
00:32:28,290 --> 00:32:30,930
I'm busy because I opened a shop.

473
00:32:30,930 --> 00:32:32,890
What kind of shop?

474
00:32:32,890 --> 00:32:34,770
[What kind of shop?]

475
00:32:34,770 --> 00:32:37,840
[Shipping notification]

476
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:40,730
[Shipping notification]

477
00:32:40,730 --> 00:32:43,600
[Hello, Black Dragon. Your order has just been shipped.]

478
00:32:45,140 --> 00:32:47,040
Finally.

479
00:33:00,990 --> 00:33:04,700
As you instructed, I cleaned everything except the study.

480
00:33:04,700 --> 00:33:08,200
Okay, thank you. You can go.

481
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:55,520
That point should be good.

482
00:33:55,520 --> 00:33:58,940
Okay. A new friend...

483
00:33:58,940 --> 00:34:00,950
Shall we get ready to welcome them?

484
00:35:11,510 --> 00:35:13,150
I'm jealous.

485
00:35:13,150 --> 00:35:16,360
To feel passionate about something.

486
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:18,960
I think it's something valuable.

487
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:21,990
Finding what you love is hard.

488
00:35:21,990 --> 00:35:25,490
It's hard to love something for a long time.

489
00:35:26,740 --> 00:35:30,970
So, enjoy it as much as you want.

490
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:59,920
[Very delicious, Sulo]

491
00:35:59,920 --> 00:36:02,070
[Grace]

492
00:36:11,010 --> 00:36:15,110
Please sign here to confirm delivery.

493
00:36:15,110 --> 00:36:17,520
Who sent all this?

494
00:36:17,520 --> 00:36:20,260
Black... Dragon?

495
00:36:20,260 --> 00:36:22,040
Ah, I understand.

496
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:23,660
Okay.

497
00:36:23,660 --> 00:36:25,250
- Go ahead. - Okay.

498
00:36:25,250 --> 00:36:27,320
Thanks.

499
00:36:28,530 --> 00:36:29,730
Have a nice day.

500
00:36:29,730 --> 00:36:32,060
- Thank you. - Of course.

501
00:36:41,910 --> 00:36:43,290
Older sister.

502
00:36:43,290 --> 00:36:44,830
What were those flowers in the front?

503
00:36:44,830 --> 00:36:46,670
Oh my, what is this?

504
00:36:46,670 --> 00:36:48,650
Why is it so cold here?

505
00:36:48,650 --> 00:36:50,070
What is this now?

506
00:36:50,070 --> 00:36:52,110
What did he bring here without telling anyone?

507
00:36:52,110 --> 00:36:54,470
I won't tell you anything.

508
00:36:54,470 --> 00:36:56,060
I asked you what it was.

509
00:36:56,060 --> 00:36:58,080
I bought it as an opening gift.

510
00:36:58,080 --> 00:37:00,730
Who would send you a gift like this?

511
00:37:00,730 --> 00:37:02,990
He looks like he came from a chaebol.

512
00:37:02,990 --> 00:37:04,480
I know.

513
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:06,690
Sit down for now.

514
00:37:06,690 --> 00:37:08,940
Let's turn off the air conditioner, sister.

515
00:37:08,940 --> 00:37:11,810
The air conditioner won't prevent it from melting.

516
00:37:11,810 --> 00:37:13,550
Should I do it?

517
00:37:14,220 --> 00:37:16,090
So, who is this?

518
00:37:16,570 --> 00:37:18,670
- A friend of mine. - Which friend?

519
00:37:18,670 --> 00:37:21,450
Do you have a friend I don't know about?

520
00:37:22,110 --> 00:37:23,970
That scared me!

521
00:37:24,930 --> 00:37:28,840
Who sent you a service robot when you didn't have any customers?

522
00:37:28,840 --> 00:37:30,080
[Congratulations on your opening, Sister]

523
00:37:31,530 --> 00:37:33,260
'Older sister'?

524
00:37:34,060 --> 00:37:35,890
From a man?

525
00:37:36,910 --> 00:37:38,240
[Wishing you endless success - Black Dragon]

526
00:37:40,490 --> 00:37:43,680
'Black Dragon'?

527
00:37:47,240 --> 00:37:50,040
I'm not going to throw away the trash and come back.

528
00:37:50,040 --> 00:37:52,050
Black Dragon?

529
00:37:52,050 --> 00:37:56,270
Sister, were you in contact with him?

530
00:37:58,430 --> 00:38:00,070
From where?

531
00:38:00,070 --> 00:38:02,900
You were angry too, because he had deceived us.

532
00:38:02,900 --> 00:38:04,350
I was angry, but...

533
00:38:04,350 --> 00:38:08,260
You know. He's a good player.

534
00:38:08,260 --> 00:38:09,710
I swear we...

535
00:38:09,710 --> 00:38:13,810
We only spoke briefly during team fights.

536
00:38:14,420 --> 00:38:16,120
I understand.

537
00:38:16,120 --> 00:38:17,700
Now I understand.

538
00:38:17,700 --> 00:38:20,140
I'm leaving. We need to keep our distance for a while.

539
00:38:20,140 --> 00:38:22,070
Strawberry. Su Jeong.

540
00:38:22,070 --> 00:38:23,460
Should I throw them all away?

541
00:38:23,460 --> 00:38:25,700
I'll throw them all away.

542
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:29,530
[Excessive drinking can cause the owner to smile.]

543
00:38:30,740 --> 00:38:32,340
Nevermind.

544
00:38:32,340 --> 00:38:34,220
Isn't it?

545
00:38:34,220 --> 00:38:36,660
Gifts. I shouldn't throw them away, should I?

546
00:38:36,660 --> 00:38:37,940
Altars Market village.

547
00:38:37,940 --> 00:38:40,690
I can't stand them, but it's a waste.

548
00:38:40,690 --> 00:38:42,490
Okay.

549
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:47,370
[Yongsung]

550
